processTETranscriptsTable <- function(file) {
    
    # This function receives as input a sigdiff_gene_TE.txt file and returns a new dataframe with correctly processed ensemblIDs.
    # Next, it subsets those genes with a log2foldchange greater than or equal to 0.56 for downstream analysis.
    # Then, it retrieves geneNames from an ENSEMBL Biomart table. 
    # Finally, it saves the processed dataframe as a csv with a meaningful name.
    # ---------------------------------------
    
    # Read .txt file
    df <- read.table(
      file,
      header = TRUE,
      row.names = NULL,
      sep = "\t"   # use "," if comma-separated
    )
    
    # Rename first column to "ensemblID"
    colnames(df)[1] <- "ensemblID"
    
    # Create regular foldChange 
    df <- df %>%
      mutate(
        foldChange   = 2^log2FoldChange
      )
    
    # Remove dot "." and following characters from ensemblID column
    df <- df %>%
      mutate(ensemblID = str_remove(ensemblID, "\\..*"))
    
    # Create df_subset, a new df that only includes sigdiff_gene_TE's >= 0.56
    df_subset <- df %>%
      filter(abs(log2FoldChange) >= 0.56)
    
    # Create df_sorted, which sorts df_subset descending by log2FoldChange
    df_sorted <- df_subset %>%
      arrange(desc(log2FoldChange))
    
    # Get gene names
    # Left join df_genes with all unique mouse gene names based on ENSEMBL id
    df_sorted <- df_sorted %>%
      left_join(
        all_unique_mouse_genes_ids_df %>%
          select(Gene.stable.ID, Gene.name),
        by = c("ensemblID" = "Gene.stable.ID")
      ) %>%
      rename(geneName = Gene.name)
    
    # Fill NA gene_ENSEMBL_join names with ENSEMBL id
    df_sorted$geneName[is.na(df_sorted$geneName)] <-
      df_sorted$ensemblID[is.na(df_sorted$geneName)]
    
    # Move geneNames col to first position
    df_final <- df_sorted %>%
      relocate(geneName)
    
    # Write csv in the current working directory
    fName = sub("\\.txt$", "", file)
    csvName = paste0(fName, "_absLog2Fold0_56_Sorted.csv")
    write.csv(df_final, file = csvName, row.names = FALSE)
    print(paste0("Successfully wrote ",csvName))
    
    # Return df_final
    df_final
}

PCA plots

See this for example: https://lashlock.github.io/compbio/R_presentation.html

In[19]:
suppressPackageStartupMessages({
    library("DESeq2")
    library("RColorBrewer")
    library("ggplot2")
})

This function receives two files as input: a count text file, and a design file. The count txt file is simply the .cntTable file renamed to a .txt file. The design file must correspond to the column names in the count.txt file. It should have a format such as this:

In[20]:
# id,dex,celltype,genotype
# t1,treated,E10,KO
# t2,treated,E10,KO
# c1,control,E10,WT
# c2,control,E10,WT

In[21]:
createPCAplot <- function(countTxtFile,designFile) {
    ##setting up DESeq dataset (dds) for unclassified samples
    GeneCountData <- read.delim(countTxtFile, header = TRUE, sep = "\t", row.names = 1)
    GeneCountDataInt <- as.matrix(GeneCountData)
    storage.mode(GeneCountDataInt) = "integer"
    Design <- read.delim(designFile, header = TRUE, sep = ",", row.names = 1)
    gdds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = GeneCountDataInt, colData = Design, design = ~dex)

    ##normalizing counts, getting size factors, and plotting PCAs for unclassified samples##
    dds_rld <- rlog(gdds)
    gdds <- estimateSizeFactors(gdds)
    factors <- sizeFactors(gdds)
    pca_unclass <- plotPCA(dds_rld, intgroup=c("celltype", "genotype"))
    ggsave(paste0(countTxtFile,".png"),plot=pca_unclass)

    plotPCA(dds_rld, intgroup=c("celltype", "genotype"))
}

Simple MA plots to visualize gene and TE expression changes

In[33]:
createMAplots <- function(cntTable,TGroupNum,CGroupNum) {
    data <- read.table(cntTable,header=T,row.names=1)
    groups <- factor(c(rep("TGroup",TGroupNum),rep("CGroup",CGroupNum)))
    min_read <- 1
    data <- data[apply(data,1,function(x){max(x)}) > min_read,]
    sampleInfo <- data.frame(groups,row.names=colnames(data))
    suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(DESeq2))
    dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = data, colData = sampleInfo, design = ~ groups)
    dds$groups = relevel(dds$groups,ref="CGroup")
    dds <- DESeq(dds)
    res <- results(dds,independentFiltering=F)
    resSig <- res[(!is.na(res$padj) & (res$padj < 0.050000) & (abs(res$log2FoldChange)> 0.000000)), ]

    ## split by TE and genes
    # Genes
    png('TEtranscripts_GRCm38_E10_777tm1d_2KO_males_vs_1WT_female_1WT_male_non_stranded_genes.png')
    res.genes = res[grep("ENSMUS", row.names(res)),]
    resSig.genes <- res.genes[(!is.na(res.genes$padj) & (res.genes$padj < 0.050000) & (abs(res.genes$log2FoldChange)> 0.000000)), ]
    plotMA(res.genes)
    library(ggplot2)
    dev.off()
    plotMA(res.genes)

    # TEs
    png('TEtranscripts_GRCm38_E10_777tm1d_2KO_males_vs_1WT_female_1WT_male_non_stranded_te.png')
    res.te = res[-grep("ENSMUS", row.names(res)),]
    resSig.te <- res.te[(!is.na(res.te$padj) & (res.te$padj < 0.050000) & (abs(res.te$log2FoldChange)> 0.000000)), ]
    plotMA(res.te)
    dev.off()
    plotMA(res.te)
}
